    "name": "Khruangbin",
    "profile": "American music band from Houston, Texas, but born in Burton, Texas. \"Khruangbin\" (\"เครื่องบิน\") translates to airplane (literal translation: \"engine fly\") in Thai. It's a homage to the Thai rock/funk that inspired the formation of the band, and the airplane symbolizes the international set of influences that shaped their music. They create and record all of their material in a barn, deep in the countryside of Texas for the tranquil and inspiring setting.",
